{"id":"natural-phenomena-8","label":"Some Natural Phenomena","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"mcq","label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions"},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"The process of transfer of charges from a charged object to the earth is called ____.","options":"earthing, lightning, electricity, circuit"},{"qText":"The power of earthquake is expressed in ____.","options":"richter scale, seismic scale, vibrating scale, Hertz"},{"qText":"Which instrument is used to measure earthquake?","options":"Seismograph, Richter Scale, Polygraph, CCTV camera"},{"qText":"Which is not a natural phenomena?","options":"Earthing, Earthquake, Cyclone, Lightning"},{"qText":"Where is the lightning rod attached to protect the building from lightning?","options":"On the top of the building, At the bottom of the building, Near the window, Near the electrical devices"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Lightning is followed by ","options":"thunder, rain, storm, cold weather"},{"qText":"Tsunami is caused by","options":"earthquake under the sea, earthquake on the seashore, eruption of volcano in a sea, a number of factors."},{"qText":"Which of the following can be charged with static electricity?","options":"Insulator, Metal, Alloy, Semiconductor"},{"qText":"Which of the following occurs during lightning?","options":"* Nitrogen Fixation, Heavy rain, Cloud Formation, None of these "},{"qText":"When two insulator bodies are rubbed against each other, they acquire _____ charges","options":"equal and unlike, equal and like, unequal and like, unequal and unlike"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"During lightning ______ takes place.","options":"electric discharge, electric charging, electric charge accumulation"},{"qText":"To protect tall building from the damage of lightning, what can be done?","options":"Install lightning arrester.\n              Have a rooftop garden.\n              Coat the top floor with insulator.\n              Install solar panal."},{"qText":"Which is the natural phenomenon we cannot predict accurately?","options":"* Earthquake, Cyclone, Thunderstorm, All of these"},{"qText":"The instrument used to dedect charged bodies is ____.","options":"barometer, *electroscope, electrometer, none of these"},{"qText":"Which of the following cannot be charged easily by friction?","options":"A copper rod, An inflated balloon, An air-filled balloon, A plastic scale"}]}]}]}